reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
Reviewed in the United States on December 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It runs well, hope it lasts
reviews.reviewText: I put this fan on MA824 stealth which is being used on the CPU heat sink, the highest rpm it shows on it was 2400, and it helps a lot, helped keeping my 14900K at 28C idle and 70C when playing game when loading but quickly dropped back to 50s

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Inaccurate Product Description
reviews.reviewText: In the title of the product it states 2400rpm fan. Mine only would go up to 1900. So I read through the description and baried at the bottom it states 0 to 1900 rpm PWM fan. Definitely not the 2400 rpm in the title.Besides that it is a pretty good fan. Just a little less performance than I expected.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars 2/6 defective, similar performance to P14 ARGB but at 25mm z-height
reviews.reviewText: Update: RMA replacement was also defective with a noisy bearing at all RPMs. 2/3 working isn't a good stat...I bought these because mounting the 27mm P14 ARGB to a radiator is a pain when the screws are 30mm long. 3mm is not a very big margin if you need a pump mount or spacer attached.The noise profile is substantially similar to the P14 ARGB as is the performance. The P14 might be slightly higher performing but it also has another 2mm to work with so I give it a pass. The LED brightness is lower % for % against the P14 but is acceptable.Quality control seems to be questionable. All five fans vibrate slightly differently, 3 of them were nearly perfect, one vibrates a little more than the others, and one makes a bearing rubbing noise at all RPMs. The noisy one is getting RMA'd as defective.The frame sits flush with radiators on the rear, but the front of the frame is recessed and leaves a gap. I presume this is so the RGB can be seen in pull applications. If you are performance minded, you may want to tape this gap up.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 22, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I’m usually picky about how the leds match and as you can see they match the color of the thermaltake fans pretty well. Unlike the Gskill ram. It’s more quiet than the thermaltake fans as described in the design description and I’m overall happy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Much Noisier Than Expected
reviews.reviewText: I am using this for a cooling fan in an electronics cabinet. Well actually, I am not using it at all, it is much noisier than I expected even on the lowest speed. I though maybe it was the cover grill, I tried three different ones, still to noisy. Moves a lot of air but at a roaring noise cost. Maybe I will try a PWM sped controller to slow it down even more, but then it won’t do the cooling task very well. Find another way.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Look great, and provides plenty of air flow
reviews.reviewText: I like these fans a lot. Though a bit pricey, they were what I was looking for. Provide some nice RGB, and plenty of air flow.Though I wish there was both a daisy-chain for power as there is for RGB, it isn't a huge deal at least for me. They look great paired with the NZXT H510 Flow.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Bought 'like brand new' used fans, these fans get returned for a reason I suppose
reviews.reviewText: One of the fans makes an abnormal noise every once in a while. The RGB tint and intensity differs between the fans. Stay away from these fans. Buy the arctic P14 ARGB instead

Very quiet and shocking amount of airflow compared to my other fans like the Corsair ML fans. The ML’s sound like my pc is taking off at higher speeds ✈️ and they don’t seem to get as much airflow as these as well as not having rgb.For rgb fans these are among the best performing, great airflow at low noise.Love that I can control the rgb with the mobo and not having to install more software. 💯.Few minor things:A pwn daisy chain would’ve made connecting other fans more of a breeze.RGB could be a little more brighter but it’s okay.Fans max out at 1900 rpm not 2400 like the ad states.Wish there was a bundle pack or something as buying individually can be costly.

the fans are quiet and pretty, good airflow you can daisy chan the 3 pin but not the 4 pins? also the cables are too long when daisy chaining leaving hanging cables but too short when you reach the end having to move some stuff and pass the cable at the front to get a good plug, having a smaller daisy chain that support both 3pin and 4pins along with an extension when you are finished should be a better alternative but beside the cable problems, this fan does its job well, quietly and looks good

reviews.reviewTitle: Good quality fan with great price to performance.
reviews.reviewText: This fans performs very well in noise controlled performance tests and they worked well on my heatsink. It has a great 0 RPM feature to be silent when your PC is idling, if you set the PWM percentage below about 15% it will stop spinning, not many fans have this easy to use feature. I control my fans with the basically named "Fan Control" software so I can have the fans be silent when my CPU and GPU aren't hot, I won't buy another fan without this feature, its great. I wish it had an extra PWM female plug so you could daisy chain fans together like my Arctic P14's but this is a more budget oriented fan. At regular price these are good but if you can get them on sale they will be great value. I hope Cooler Master makes a 140mm version of this fan.

Très bonne fan ARGB. Une des plus efficaces sur le marché présentement côté rpm et airflow. Un peu dispendieux mais en vaut la peine si vous cherchez productivité et à la fois bonne qualité de lumière. Moins coloré que d'autre marque mais la performance est inégalée.Pro:-Silencieuse-Bon airflow-PrixCon:-les branchements ne sont pas très long-ARGB n'est pas la meilleure question éclairage
